Author: Komodo-Bot#0171
Content: [B. G√ºltekin √áetiner#0626] I cannot share the chart but there is interesting statistics. The crypto ownership is highest with 18%  in Turkey than in USA and Europe. And 1 of 2 considers buying crypto. There is more. Trust in crypto is highest in Turkey. If Turkey is to be ground zero in the global financial crisis as James Rickards suggested, I think Turkey is more likely to be a paradigm frontier rather than being a canary in mining field. The reason for this might be we have already a system where people can create money in a non-digital blokchain. It was invented very long time ago. How does it work? I simply write the amount on a check and pay you. You sign it make payment to somebody else. It has a chain of signatures on the paper. Sometimes the paper does not fit. They stick additional paper on it to keep the chain. We definitely need talented developers. I think #chainzilla type approach will speed up the processes. If people discover the power of Komodo in Turkey it would help paradigm change a lot.
